### TON Blockchain Integration Tests
### Используйте в VS Code с расширением REST Client или в WebStorm/IntelliJ IDEA

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@testSellerAddress = EQD4FPq-PRDieyQKkizFTRtSDyucUIqrj0v_zXJmqaDp6_0t
@testBuyerAddress = EQCD39VS5jcptHL8vMjEXrzGaRcCVYto7HUn4bpAOg8xqB2N

### ==============================================
### 1. Health Check - Проверка подключения к TON
### ==============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/health
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 2. Validate Address - Проверка валидности адреса
### ==============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/validate/{{testSellerAddress}}
Accept: application/json

### Invalid address test
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/validate/INVALID_ADDRESS
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 3. Get Balance - Получить баланс адреса
### ==============================================

# Замените на реальный адрес admin wallet после настройки
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/balance/EQBIhPuWmjT7fP-VomuTWseE8JNWv2q7QYfsVQ1IZwnMk8wL
Accept: application/json

### Test seller balance
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/balance/{{testSellerAddress}}
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 4. Deploy Escrow Contract - Деплой контракта
### ==============================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/deploy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sellerAddress": "{{testSellerAddress}}",
  "buyerAddress": "{{testBuyerAddress}}",
  "amount": 1,
  "timeoutSeconds": 2592000
}

### После деплоя сохраните contractAddress из ответа
### и замените в следующих запросах

@contractAddress = EQBxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

### ==============================================
### 5. Get Contract State - Состояние контракта
### ==============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/{{contractAddress}}
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 6. Check if Contract Deployed
### ==============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/contract/{{contractAddress}}/deployed
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 7. Get Contract Transactions
### ==============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/transactions/{{contractAddress}}
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### 8. Release Funds (Admin operation)
### ==============================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/{{contractAddress}}/release
Content-Type: application/json

### ==============================================
### 9. Refund Funds (Admin operation)
### ==============================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/{{contractAddress}}/refund
Content-Type: application/json

### ==============================================
### Full Flow Test Example
### ==============================================

### Step 1: Deploy contract
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/deploy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sellerAddress": "{{testSellerAddress}}",
  "buyerAddress": "{{testBuyerAddress}}",
  "amount": 0.1,
  "timeoutSeconds": 86400
}

###

### Step 2: Get contract state (should be "created")
# Замените CONTRACT_ADDRESS на адрес из предыдущего ответа
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/CONTRACT_ADDRESS
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 3: Buyer sends funds (делается через TON Wallet)
# Через Tonkeeper отправьте amount TON на адрес CONTRACT_ADDRESS
# В комментарии укажите: 1 (OP code для fund)

###

### Step 4: Check state again (should be "funded" after buyer payment)
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/CONTRACT_ADDRESS
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 5: Release to seller (after buyer confirms)
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/CONTRACT_ADDRESS/release
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 6: Final state check (should be "released")
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/CONTRACT_ADDRESS
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### Error Cases Tests
### ==============================================

### Test 1: Deploy without balance (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/deploy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sellerAddress": "{{testSellerAddress}}",
  "buyerAddress": "{{testBuyerAddress}}",
  "amount": 1000000,
  "timeoutSeconds": 2592000
}

###

### Test 2: Release before funding (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/escrow/EQB_NOT_FUNDED_CONTRACT/release
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Test 3: Invalid address
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockchain/balance/INVALID
Accept: application/json

### ==============================================
### Integration with Transactions API
### ==============================================

### Create transaction (requires JWT auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "listing_id": "listing-uuid-here"
}

###

### Get transaction details
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions/transaction-uuid-here
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Confirm transaction (buyer confirms receipt)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions/transaction-uuid-here/confirm
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer BUYER_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "rating": 5,
  "comment": "Excellent seller!"
}

###

### Open dispute
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions/transaction-uuid-here/dispute
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer BUYER_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "reason": "Item not as described"
}

###

### Resolve dispute (admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/disputes/transaction-uuid-here/resolve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "resolution": "refund_buyer",
  "comment": "Buyer is right, refunding"
}
